                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities, 1931/198:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-20T12:00:00-05:45"
                            >July 20, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 11:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. My 139, July 16, 10 a.m. Guardia patrol reconnoitering from Cape Gracias up
                    the Coco River was attacked July 17th by bandits, estimated at 40, and 3 bandits
                    were killed. A Nicaraguan officer of the Guardia was wounded. The reconnaissance
                    of that region by Guardia and airplanes is continuing and more definite
                    information concerning the situation is expected soon. One Guardia was wounded
                    at Rama yesterday in a conflict between the Guardia and what is believed to be
                    discontented unemployed labor. It is reported that the Guardia restored order
                    but the small detachment at Rama is being reenforced from Bluefields.</p>
                <p>The foregoing is to forestall possible sensational reports to the United States
                    from the east coast.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
